{"session_id":"svc-1778456008814848720","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-10T23:33:30.836847056Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-09ceb430-20260510T233326-b4925cc5","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-09ceb430\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003efeat(work): ddx work analyze CLI for cross-attempt performance queries\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  After sister bead extracts per-attempt metrics to\u0026#xA;  .ddx/metrics/attempts.jsonl, operators need a query tool to\u0026#xA;  read it. Without a CLI, optimization signals are unused: the\u0026#xA;  data exists but answering \u0026#34;which model has the best\u0026#xA;  cost-per-success?\u0026#34; requires manual jq scripting per query.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CURRENT STATE\u0026#xA;  - No ddx subcommand reads .ddx/metrics/.\u0026#xA;  - No documented query patterns for cross-attempt analysis.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  Implement ddx work analyze with the following query dimensions\u0026#xA;  and aggregations:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Dimensions (--by \u0026lt;dim\u0026gt; or composable):\u0026#xA;    - model\u0026#xA;    - harness\u0026#xA;    - profile\u0026#xA;    - prompt_template_hash\u0026#xA;    - spec_id\u0026#xA;    - outcome\u0026#xA;    - bead_id\u0026#xA;    - day / week / month (by ts_start bucket)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Aggregations (printed as columns):\u0026#xA;    - count(attempts)\u0026#xA;    - success_rate (closed-merged / total)\u0026#xA;    - avg cost_usd, sum cost_usd\u0026#xA;    - p50/p95 duration_ms\u0026#xA;    - avg input_tokens, output_tokens\u0026#xA;    - review_block_rate\u0026#xA;    - escalation_rate (ladder_steps_taken \u0026gt; 0)\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Output format:\u0026#xA;    - Default: human-readable table to stdout.\u0026#xA;    - --json: emit JSON rows for piping to other tools.\u0026#xA;    - --csv: emit CSV for spreadsheet import.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Examples:\u0026#xA;    ddx work analyze --by model\u0026#xA;        → rows: model, count, success_rate, avg_cost, ...\u0026#xA;    ddx work analyze --by model,outcome\u0026#xA;        → rows: model+outcome combos\u0026#xA;    ddx work analyze --by spec_id --since 7d\u0026#xA;        → recent week, by spec\u0026#xA;    ddx work analyze --where model=claude-sonnet-4-6 --by prompt_template_hash\u0026#xA;        → drill into a specific model\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Implementation:\u0026#xA;    - cli/cmd/work_analyze.go (new file).\u0026#xA;    - Reads .ddx/metrics/attempts.jsonl in full (or partition\u0026#xA;      files if multi-machine arrives later).\u0026#xA;    - In-memory aggregation (millions of rows fit; this is not\u0026#xA;      a database).\u0026#xA;    - Pure-Go, no external deps.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;  Tests:\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_ByModel\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_BySpecId\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_ComposedDimensions\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_SinceFilter\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_WhereFilter\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_JSONOutput\u0026#xA;    - TestAnalyze_CSVOutput\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - SQL or declarative query language (too much for v1).\u0026#xA;  - Live dashboards / web UI (separate concern).\u0026#xA;  - Cross-machine aggregation (deferred until federation\u0026#xA;    + partition).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - Sister bead \u0026#34;feat(metrics): extract per-attempt rows\u0026#34; —\u0026#xA;    this bead reads the output of that one.\u0026#xA;  - ADR bead documents this as the analytics entrypoint.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/cmd/work_analyze.go implements ddx work analyze with --by \u0026lt;dim\u0026gt;, --since \u0026lt;duration\u0026gt;, --where \u0026lt;key\u0026gt;=\u0026lt;value\u0026gt;, --json, --csv flags.\u0026#xA;2. Supported dimensions: model, harness, profile, prompt_template_hash, spec_id, outcome, bead_id, day, week, month.\u0026#xA;3. Supported aggregations: count, success_rate, avg cost_usd, sum cost_usd, p50/p95 duration_ms, avg tokens, review_block_rate, escalation_rate.\u0026#xA;4. Default output is human-readable table; --json emits JSONL; --csv emits CSV.\u0026#xA;5. TestAnalyze_ByModel, TestAnalyze_BySpecId, TestAnalyze_ComposedDimensions, TestAnalyze_SinceFilter, TestAnalyze_WhereFilter, TestAnalyze_JSONOutput, TestAnalyze_CSVOutput all pass.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... green.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:agent, area:metrics, kind:feature\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"22110755e9825476d2e724bcfd3661baa667c148\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260510T233326-b4925cc5","base_rev":"22110755e9825476d2e724bcfd3661baa667c148","bead_id":"ddx-09ceb430","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5","correlation_id":"ddx-09ceb430:20260510T233326-b4925cc5","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260510T233326-b4925cc5/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"151d200caa5f13d9c2e53b54fafefb64dd164496c0b4843cfff7f2d9cb5d32b5","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-e168d62f","worker_id":""}}}
